:0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"13731","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13731"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.06,0.09,0.72,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6350"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47848"}}}},{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261074"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:38:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T07:40:20+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":19,"questionsAnswered":7,"marksTotal":19,"marksAttainable":7,"marksAttempted":7,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T07:39:59+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.14,"questionsCorrect":1,"marksCorrect":1},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"items","id":"6350","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6350"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13731"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"32591"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"11198"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"11802"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31698"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47848","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/47848"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 10-year-old girl presents to her General Practice clinic with her parents with a six-month history of an erythematous rash on her face, chest, and hands, as well as progressive proximal muscle weakness. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well. Her vital signs are within normal limits. She has an erythematous, scaly rash on her upper eyelids bilaterally, and erythematous papules overlying the metacarpophalangeal and interphalangeal joints. Neurological examination reveals symmetrical proximal muscle weakness in the upper and lower limbs.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Systemic lupus erythematosus","Polymyositis","Juvenile idiopathic arthritis","Dermatomyositis","Mixed connective tissue disease"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical presentation is most consistent with a diagnosis of \u003Cstrong\u003Edermatomyositis\u003C/strong\u003E. Dermatomyositis is an idiopathic inflammatory myopathy characterised by proximal muscle weakness and pathognomonic skin findings. The characteristic rash includes an erythematous rash on the upper eyelids (heliotrope rash) and erythematous papules overlying the knuckles (Gottron\u0027s papules). Muscle weakness is typically symmetrical and affects proximal muscle groups.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESystemic lupus erythematosus (SLE)\u003C/strong\u003E can present with similar skin and muscle findings. However, the presence of the heliotrope rash and Gottron\u0027s papules is more specific for dermatomyositis. SLE would also be expected to have multi-system involvement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPolymyositis\u003C/strong\u003E is another idiopathic inflammatory myopathy that presents with proximal muscle weakness. However, it is not associated with the characteristic skin findings seen in dermatomyositis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJuvenile idiopathic arthritis (JIA)\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with joint pain, swelling, and stiffness. While some subtypes of JIA can have skin involvement, the characteristic findings of dermatomyositis would not be expected.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMixed connective tissue disease\u003C/strong\u003E is an overlap syndrome with features of SLE, systemic sclerosis, and polymyositis. While muscle weakness can be a feature, the skin findings are more consistent with dermatomyositis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Dermatomyositis is an idiopathic inflammatory myopathy characterised by proximal muscle weakness and pathognomonic skin findings.","The characteristic rash of dermatomyositis includes Gottron\u0027s papules and a heliotrope rash."],"references":["Hutchinson C, Feldman BM. Juvenile dermatomyositis and other idiopathic inflammatory myopathies: Diagnosis. In: UpToDate [online]. 2024. Available at: https://www.uptodate.com/contents/juvenile-dermatomyositis-and-other-idiopathic-inflammatory-myopathies-diagnosis","Gupta P, Shruti S, Chaudhary V, Khullar G, Siraj F. Juvenile Dermatomyositis: A Case Report and Review of Literature. Cureus. 2019 Jan 22;11(1):e3935. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6433086/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"32591"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13731"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"32591","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/32591"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-06-30T15:04:23+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-08-03T09:28:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6350"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"47848"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonym